</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="172" pageNumber="173" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,150,2014]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,679,1446,1473]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Pile Perch</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[732,824,1447,1473]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.42" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="cm" value="44.2">44.2 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[841,923,1447,1474]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4196" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="in" value="17.4">17.4 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[989,1229,1447,1473]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Southern British Columbia (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[485,544,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
2002) to Bahía Playa Maria (
<geoCoordinate box="[890,990,1482,1509]" degrees="28" direction="north" minutes="52" orientation="latitude" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" precision="925" value="28.866667">28°52’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1004,1122,1483,1509]" degrees="114" direction="west" minutes="30" orientation="longitude" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" precision="925" value="-114.5">114°30’W</geoCoordinate>
) (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California) on mainland, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1258,1432,1519,1545]" name="Isla Guadalupe" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Isla Guadalupe</collectingCountry>
, central Baja California (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[474,716,1555,1581]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingCountry box="[787,827,1555,1581]" name="Iceland" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Isla</collectingCountry>
de Cedros and 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1050,1555,1581]" name="Iceland" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Isla</collectingCountry>
Natividad (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramirez-Valdez" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ramirez-Valdez" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="143 - 167" refId="ref315365" refString="Ramirez-Valdez, A., Aburto-Oropeza, O., Palacios-Salgado, D. S., Reyes-Bonilla, H., Dominguez Guerro, I., Hinojosa Arango, G., Correa S., F., Villasenor-Derbez, J. C., Cota-Nieto, J. J. &amp; Hernadez-Velasco, A. (2015) The nearshore fishes of the Cedros Archipelago (north-eastern Pacific) and their biogeographic affinities. CalCOFI Reports, 56, 143 - 167." type="journal article" year="2015">
Ramírez-Valdez 
<emphasis box="[1378,1437,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). A reported occurrence from Wrangell, south-eastern Alaska lacks documentation (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[1378,1437,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
2002). Depth: intertidal to 
<quantity box="[506,579,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3199999999999998" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="132.0">132 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[596,668,1627,1654]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.319784" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="ft" value="433.0">433 ft</quantity>
) (min.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Chotkowski" box="[761,965,1627,1653]" firstAuthor="Chotkowski" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" refId="ref270379" refString="Chotkowski, M. A. (1994) The Behavioral Ecology and Population Dynamics of the Intertidal Fishes of the Northeast Pacific. Ph. D. Thesis, University of California, Los Angeles." type="book" year="1994">Chotkowski 1994</bibRefCitation>
; max.: DFO); reported to 
<quantity box="[1267,1340,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="210.0">210 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1357,1429,1627,1654]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1031199999999997" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="ft" value="690.0">690 ft</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Love" box="[206,399,1662,1689]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Love" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" refId="ref297693" refString="Love, M. S., Mecklenburg, C. W., Mecklenburg, T. A. &amp; Thorsteinson, L. K. (2005) Resource inventory of marine and estuarine fishes of the West Coast and Alaska: a checklist of North Pacific and Arctic Ocean species from Baja California to the Alaska-Yukon Border. United States Department of the Interior, United States Geological Survey, Biological Resources Divition, Seattle, OCS Study MMS 2005 - 030 and USGS / NBII 2005 - 001." type="book" year="2005">
Love 
<emphasis box="[273,331,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
), but apparently without documentation. Recently as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Girard, 1854)" baseAuthorityName="Girard" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[1004,1388,1662,1689]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Embiotocidae" genus="Rhacochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vacca">
<emphasis box="[1004,1216,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Rhacochilus vacca</emphasis>
(Girard, 1854)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Girard, 1854" authorityName="Girard" authorityYear="1854" box="[198,579,1698,1725]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Embiotocidae" genus="Damalichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vacca">
<emphasis box="[198,426,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Damalichthys vacca</emphasis>
Girard, 1854
</taxonomicName>
. We follow the genetic studies of 
<bibRefCitation author="Longo and Bernardi" box="[968,1278,1698,1725]" firstAuthor="Longo" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref296858" refString="Longo, G. &amp; Bernardi, G. (2015) The evolutionary history of the embiotocid surfperch radiation based on genome-wide RAD sequence data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 88, 55 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2015.03.027" type="journal article" year="2015">Longo and Bernardi (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Longo" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Longo" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="591 - 596" refId="ref296910" refString="Longo, G. C., Bernardi, G. &amp; Lea, R. N. (2018) Taxonomic revisions within Embiotocidae (Teleostei, Perciformes) based on molecular phylogenetics. Zootaxa, 4482, 591 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4482.3.10" type="journal article" year="2018">
Longo 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and place this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Girard" authorityYear="1854" box="[706,843,1735,1761]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Embiotocidae" genus="Phanerodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,843,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Phanerodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
